NAME
   mnttsk_gsm - Initialization Task For General Status Message
                Related Items

SYNOPSIS
   mnttsk_gsm [-t action] [-h]

DESCRIPTION

This process performs ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA LB file initialization.

The startup action can take on one of the following values:  "startup",
"restart", and "clear".  For each action, the following steps are performed: 

   startup:

      1)  The VOL_STAT_GSM_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is read.  
          If the message exists, the initial volume flag is set, then the 
          LB message is written back to the LB.  If the message does not
          exist, then the message is initialized with defaults.  The format 
          of this message is defined in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

      2)  The RDA_STATUS_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is 
          initialized with defaults.  The format of this message is defined 
          in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

      3)  The ARCHIII_STATUS_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is read.
          If the message exists, no initialization is performed.  Otherwise,
          the message is initialized with defaults.  The format of this message
          is defined in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

      4)  The SCAN_SUMMARY_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is read.
          If the message exists, no action is taken.  If the message does
          not exist, then the data is initialized with defaults.  The 
          format of this message is defined in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

   restart:

      1)  The VOL_STAT_GSM_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is read.  
          If the message exists, the initial volume flag is set, then the 
          LB message is written back to the LB.  If the message does not
          exist, then the message is initialized with defaults.  The format 
          of this message is defined in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

      2)  The RDA_STATUS_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is 
          initialized with defaults.  The format of this message is defined 
          in header file gen_stat_msg.h.

      3)  The ARCHIII_STATUS_ID LB message of LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA is read.
          If the data exists, no initialization is performed.  Otherwise, the 
          message is initialized with defaults.  The format of this message is 
          defined in header file gen_stat_msg.h.
  

   clear:

      All LB messages within LB ID ORPGDAT_GSM_DATA are removed.

   Options
	-t mode		startup mode.  Determines which initialization actions to
                        be performed.  Supported startup modes are "startup" and
                        "restart".  By default, the mode is "restart".  

	-h		Provides command line help.


